Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

18
00:01:06,867 --> 00:01:08,352
<i>...That's when my day starts.</i>
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

19
00:01:08,352 --> 00:01:12,180
Director: MATSUOKA JOJI
Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne
<i>Always seems like a thing of the past</i>

20
00:01:12,180 --> 00:01:17,743
Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne
<i>Always seems like a thing of the past</i>

21
00:01:18,439 --> 00:01:29,000
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

22
00:01:32,472 --> 00:01:38,140
<i>My business hours start from midnight to 7 am.</i>

23
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:41,960
<i>People call my restaurant 'the late night diner.'</i>

24
00:01:43,082 --> 00:01:44,769
[Pork Miso Soup Set ¥600, Beer ¥600, Sake ¥500, Shochu ¥400,
Alcoholic drinks are limited to 3 servings]

25
00:01:44,769 --> 00:01:46,906
<i>These are the only items on the menu.</i>
[Pork Miso Soup Set ¥600, Beer ¥600, Sake ¥500, Shochu ¥400,
Alcoholic drinks are limited to 3 servings]

26
00:01:46,906 --> 00:01:49,962
<i>If one orders something aside from these...</i>

27
00:01:49,962 --> 00:01:52,259
<i>...I'll make it if I can.</i>

28
00:01:52,259 --> 00:01:54,840
<i>Such is my business philosophy.</i>

29
00:01:56,077 --> 00:01:58,840
[MESHIYA]

30
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:03,610
<i>Do customers come? You ask...
There's quite a number who do.</i>

31
00:02:05,244 --> 00:02:13,724
<i>Wabi-Sabi Subs presents:</i>
<b>SHINYA SHOKUDO Season 3</b>
EP 10: "Crossing the Year Soba..."

32
00:02:20,716 --> 00:02:24,739
<i>On New Year's Eve, I open
the shop earlier than usual.</i>

33
00:02:25,075 --> 00:02:26,372
<i>Why, you ask?</i>

34
00:02:26,653 --> 00:02:29,916
<i>There's quite a number of customers
who spend New Year's Eve at my shop.</i>

35
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:34,136
<i>That's why I have make to
preparations ahead of time.</i>

36
00:02:36,026 --> 00:02:38,216
So you were born in Aizu (in Fukushima), huh?

37
00:02:38,216 --> 00:02:40,086
It's pretty obvious from my
license plate, isn't it?

38
00:02:40,296 --> 00:02:41,976
Well, yes.

39
00:02:42,401 --> 00:02:44,691
Is there a problem with
the prefecture number?

40
00:02:45,330 --> 00:02:48,528
I wonder if you were taught this in school...

41
00:02:48,528 --> 00:02:51,950
Don't you know the "Beware of incoming guns and
outgoing women" policy? You know...

42
00:02:51,950 --> 00:02:54,661
"Outgoing women" as in women leaving.
(Note: During the Edo period, guards are tasked to watch out for guns coming in the capital, and warlords' wives leaving which might be signs of a rebellion against the Shogunate)

43
00:02:54,661 --> 00:02:56,302
How should I know...

44
00:02:56,302 --> 00:02:58,726
I like Urabandai (in Fukushima).

45
00:02:58,726 --> 00:03:02,956
My uncle's second wife's cousin is
from Nekoma (also in Urabandai, Fukushima).

46
00:03:02,956 --> 00:03:05,076
But I only stopped for a minute...

47
00:03:05,286 --> 00:03:07,546
The law is strict, isn't it?

48
00:03:08,126 --> 00:03:09,716
Can you please overlook i~t?

49
00:03:11,326 --> 00:03:14,186
Those words aren't altogether bad.

50
00:03:15,858 --> 00:03:16,898
So it's okay?

51
00:03:17,309 --> 00:03:19,919
I can't help but like the sound of it.

52
00:03:20,194 --> 00:03:23,204
When someone is driven to a corner,
he stretches out the last syllable.

53
00:03:23,715 --> 00:03:25,415
Here you go, sir.

54
00:03:53,422 --> 00:03:54,472
Welcome.

55
00:03:54,787 --> 00:03:59,166
You're open even on New Year's Eve?
It's "no leisure for the poor" for you, too huh?

56
00:03:59,166 --> 00:04:02,286
Do you want to eat Crossing-the-Year Soba?
I just made a fresh batch.

57
00:04:03,186 --> 00:04:06,446
Already been given enough soba.
You can have it.

58
00:04:06,446 --> 00:04:08,516
Besides, I only eat udon.

59
00:04:15,686 --> 00:04:16,816
Thank you.

60
00:04:17,126 --> 00:04:20,451
In exchange, I'll treat you
to some benishoga tempura.

61
00:04:20,451 --> 00:04:24,486
Maybe next time. I'm busy today.

62
00:04:24,486 --> 00:04:25,486
You have work?

63
00:04:25,486 --> 00:04:28,556
Well, something like that. This period
is a good time to make a profit.

64
00:04:28,726 --> 00:04:29,536
See you.

65
00:04:36,566 --> 00:04:44,216
Kasumi-san! You're leaving already?

66
00:04:41,526 --> 00:04:44,216
You reacted too early.

67
00:04:44,366 --> 00:04:48,316
In life, timing is everything.

68
00:04:48,885 --> 00:04:50,785
You can't rely on luck alone.

69
00:04:51,322 --> 00:04:52,842
Well then, Happy New Year.

70
00:04:53,143 --> 00:04:54,593
Happy New Year, too.

71
00:05:02,171 --> 00:05:05,076
In Osaka, they eat
Crossing-the-Year Udon instead, right?

72
00:05:05,466 --> 00:05:09,306
Well, I wonder...

73
00:05:10,526 --> 00:05:14,886
Master, can you give me
Kasumi-san's soba?

74
00:05:15,393 --> 00:05:16,953
She didn't make it though.

75
00:05:17,126 --> 00:05:18,568
It's okay.

76
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:23,750
I'll feel that a bond between us will be
born through that soba.

77
00:05:25,675 --> 00:05:27,195
I don't mind though.

78
00:05:30,646 --> 00:05:32,196
Good evening.

79
00:05:32,735 --> 00:05:34,135
Welcome.

80
00:05:34,486 --> 00:05:37,446
How rare of you two
coming in together.

81
00:05:37,446 --> 00:05:39,916
We just happened to meet at the station.

82
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:44,248
It's handmade soba.
My client gave it to me.

83
00:05:44,248 --> 00:05:48,806
Mine, too. My boss makes exquisite soba and
insists that I should try it.

84
00:05:48,806 --> 00:05:51,036
So you want me to cook them?

85
00:05:51,286 --> 00:05:53,046
He wants to know what I think of it.

86
00:05:53,046 --> 00:05:59,856
Same for me. We'd like to eat it later, so
we'll leave this with you now to take care of?

87
00:06:00,038 --> 00:06:02,168
Thanks.

88
00:06:07,027 --> 00:06:09,317
It's true that homemade soba
is popular, huh?

89
00:06:09,901 --> 00:06:12,556
It's become the hobby of the retired man.

90
00:06:12,556 --> 00:06:15,846
There's been a lot of training
courses and even lessons on DVD.

91
00:06:15,846 --> 00:06:19,274
It also doesn't require much money,
and you do get kinda fixated on it.

92
00:06:19,274 --> 00:06:21,584
Its meaning is quite profound
as well, isn't it?

93
00:06:22,035 --> 00:06:26,425
But still I wonder if we'll become like
that too when we get old.

94
00:06:26,606 --> 00:06:30,616
We definitely will, once things
start to not go so well at home.

95
00:06:31,406 --> 00:06:35,266
But even if we don't have a family...

96
00:06:35,266 --> 00:06:38,226
Though it's New Year's Eve,
we're here, right?

97
00:06:38,226 --> 00:06:40,836
We're spending it together
again this year, huh?

98
00:06:50,723 --> 00:06:52,645
- It's good.
- Mine, too.

99
00:06:56,380 --> 00:06:58,450
- So early!
- Welcome.

100
00:06:58,940 --> 00:07:00,020
Here, Master.

101
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:02,750
Don't tell me this is...

102
00:07:03,151 --> 00:07:05,233
I got it from a patient.

103
00:07:05,234 --> 00:07:09,443
He said he was able to get soba from the famous shop in
Nagano that you're only able to get enough for one person.

104
00:07:09,442 --> 00:07:11,242
Can you cook it quickly?

105
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:13,880
Master, make mine with tempura.
How about you, Kimi-kun?

106
00:07:14,077 --> 00:07:15,777
With egg for me.

107
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:17,863
Sure thing.

108
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:24,730
- Delicious, right?
- It sure is!

109
00:07:24,895 --> 00:07:26,642
It's quite firm and tasty.

110
00:07:26,642 --> 00:07:28,072
Let's exchange for a bit.

111
00:07:31,366 --> 00:07:34,206
Kimi-kun, can I eat the yolk?

112
00:07:34,363 --> 00:07:35,343
Sure.

113
00:07:38,423 --> 00:07:40,383
There's nothing to do anymore.

114
00:07:41,979 --> 00:07:43,119
Why don't we just drink?

115
00:07:44,020 --> 00:07:45,030
Yeah.

116
00:07:45,266 --> 00:07:48,886
Master, ginger ale and beer.

117
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:50,500
Sure thing.

118
00:08:02,353 --> 00:08:03,303
Wanna play?

119
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:06,920
You don't, right?

120
00:08:09,140 --> 00:08:12,740
What's with you, boys?
Sitting together with long faces like that.

121
00:08:12,740 --> 00:08:14,590
Come on. Let's play.

122
00:08:14,790 --> 00:08:16,472
- You want to play?
- Yeah. We do, right?

123
00:08:16,472 --> 00:08:17,820
Oh, of course.

124
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:18,710
Let's play.

125
00:08:31,370 --> 00:08:32,810
Oh, you're the Old Maid.

126
00:08:32,910 --> 00:08:34,140
No peeking please.

127
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:39,280
Okay okay.

128
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:41,990
Kimi-kun, which one will you pick?

129
00:08:43,459 --> 00:08:45,629
Master, gimme hot liquor.

130
00:08:46,278 --> 00:08:47,417
Sure thing.

131
00:08:47,417 --> 00:08:50,090
It's quite cold outside.

132
00:08:50,090 --> 00:08:52,650
You should just stay at home and sleep under
the kotatsu. You're going to catch a cold again.

133
00:08:52,851 --> 00:08:53,891
No mistaking that.

134
00:08:54,068 --> 00:08:55,108
You went around town?

135
00:08:55,604 --> 00:08:58,583
Just a while ago, I ended up spending
the otoshidama* at the pachinko shop.
(*money gifts for children; it probably means he
gambled away the money meant for his grandkids)

136
00:08:58,583 --> 00:09:00,671
My chest already feels cold.

137
00:09:00,671 --> 00:09:02,091
Do you wanna join in?

138
00:09:02,481 --> 00:09:05,536
Really, guys. What're you doing
on this New Year's Eve...

139
00:09:05,536 --> 00:09:07,766
This ain't a middle school excursion.

140
00:09:08,654 --> 00:09:10,464
There's nothing to do.

141
00:09:11,169 --> 00:09:15,153
Well, even so.
Oh, I almost forgot...

142
00:09:15,153 --> 00:09:16,443
Excuse me for a while.

143
00:09:17,484 --> 00:09:20,674
Master, I received this from my hometown.

144
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:23,080
It's made with soba flour
so it's a bit dry but...

145
00:09:23,261 --> 00:09:26,451
I still want to eat it sometimes.
If you could please cook it for me...

146
00:09:35,606 --> 00:09:36,986
Thanks for waiting.

147
00:09:37,609 --> 00:09:39,669
Okay, time out first. Time out.

148
00:09:52,954 --> 00:09:56,014
Aren't you gonna chew?
Chuu-san, you might choke on it.

149
00:09:56,157 --> 00:10:00,237
You see, the way to savor soba is
to let it slide down your throat.

150
00:10:03,496 --> 00:10:04,536
Welcome.

151
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,330
Good evening.

152
00:10:09,604 --> 00:10:12,904
Crossing-the-Year Zaru Soba* please, for three.
(*without soup)

153
00:10:17,327 --> 00:10:19,347
Oh, can you make it to go?

154
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:22,917
You want MY soba?

155
00:10:24,551 --> 00:10:26,431
Well, of course.

156
00:10:29,550 --> 00:10:30,760
Sure thing!

157
00:10:57,990 --> 00:11:02,680
This wasabi was raised in a clear stream,
a natural product of Amagi (Shizuoka prefecture).

158
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:04,020
Please.

159
00:11:05,070 --> 00:11:08,450
You can either dissolve it in the sauce
or put it on your soba.

160
00:11:09,071 --> 00:11:11,351
Thank you~.

161
00:11:12,430 --> 00:11:16,400
It's handmade soba with authentic wasabi.
Isn't this quite a luxury?

162
00:11:16,590 --> 00:11:19,270
We usually only eat soba
from stand-only stalls...

163
00:11:19,270 --> 00:11:24,460
In the past, soba was originally food for common people.
It's shameful to not eat it at those stand-only stalls.

164
00:11:28,274 --> 00:11:31,734
Now is the time that it's super spicy.
Please don't slurp it all at once.

165
00:11:32,279 --> 00:11:34,259
You shoulda told me earlier!

166
00:11:44,687 --> 00:11:47,477
The year is already ending.

167
00:11:58,669 --> 00:12:01,089
Sliding to home base... safe!

168
00:12:01,089 --> 00:12:03,489
- We made it in time.
- Welcome.

169
00:12:03,820 --> 00:12:05,880
Kosuzu-san, what about your shop?

170
00:12:06,083 --> 00:12:11,473
I want to spend the New Year here, so I kicked out
my stubborn customers and closed the shop.

171
00:12:12,111 --> 00:12:14,481
Master, one bowl of soba please.

172
00:12:15,110 --> 00:12:16,940
- How about you, Koucchan?
- Can I have jumbo size?

173
00:12:17,150 --> 00:12:20,620
Of course. Master, one jumbo bowl please.

174
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:22,740
- Sure thing.
- Can I have hot soba?

175
00:12:22,870 --> 00:12:23,540
Me too!

176
00:12:23,540 --> 00:12:26,490
This time, I want the ones you made, Master.

177
00:12:26,599 --> 00:12:27,449
Same goes for us.

178
00:12:27,710 --> 00:12:29,920
Guess I'll have some, too.
Make it light.

179
00:12:30,132 --> 00:12:31,332
Sure thing!

180
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:49,756
Everyone, I wish you all
a Happy New Year.

181
00:12:49,756 --> 00:12:52,036
Happy New Year!

182
00:12:52,591 --> 00:12:54,120
Hoping for your continued patronage.

183
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:55,560
- Best regards, too.
- Let's continue to get along.

184
00:12:55,560 --> 00:13:00,458
- Let's have a great year.
- Peaceful year to you.

185
00:13:01,464 --> 00:13:03,864
Thank you so much.

186
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:15,110
Here you go.

187
00:13:17,101 --> 00:13:23,711
Well, so then... Instead of a New Year's
greeting, let's make a toast.

188
00:13:26,550 --> 00:13:29,220
- Hang on--
- Wait for us!

189
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,620
Thank you~.

190
00:13:32,180 --> 00:13:35,630
Then, to a new start... Cheers!

191
00:13:35,630 --> 00:13:37,208
Cheers!

192
00:13:37,208 --> 00:13:38,660
[Alcoholic drinks are limited to 3 servings]

193
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:41,259
[Happy New Year]

194
00:13:43,104 --> 00:13:44,794
Is it okay, Master?

195
00:13:45,596 --> 00:13:48,626
This is my New Year's gift to you all.

196
00:13:56,149 --> 00:13:57,819
Ryucchan!

197
00:13:58,102 --> 00:13:59,142
It's ready.

198
00:14:13,678 --> 00:14:14,968
You try it.

199
00:14:15,070 --> 00:14:16,400
Go ahead! Go ahead!

200
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:18,700
- I do wanna try!
- Do your best!

201
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:19,720
Do your best!

202
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:20,840
Ready, set...

203
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:26,510
I'm doing it! I'm doing it!

204
00:14:30,152 --> 00:14:31,680
Next, Master.

205
00:14:31,680 --> 00:14:32,738
Go, Master!

206
00:14:32,738 --> 00:14:36,198
No thanks. I have to make
the preparations now.

207
00:14:37,012 --> 00:14:38,892
For this?
(*To make zoni or rice cake soup)

208
00:14:40,030 --> 00:14:41,760
Then, I'll do it instead.

209
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:44,450
You can do it, Sister!

210
00:15:02,185 --> 00:15:04,815
You're affected by these
lovebirds beside me, right?

211
00:15:05,509 --> 00:15:12,389
Don't worry. 'Cause you'll meet a good man
this year, and get married.

212
00:15:13,435 --> 00:15:15,245
It's not that.

213
00:15:15,666 --> 00:15:21,856
It's just... I feel so happy
being with everyone like this.

214
00:15:22,885 --> 00:15:28,335
You're right. This is what you call
"an irreplaceable time."

215
00:15:28,870 --> 00:15:32,610
Yeah, I think so too.

216
00:15:32,787 --> 00:15:39,437
And, to think that sooner or later,
everyone of us will die one by one...

217
00:15:39,646 --> 00:15:41,506
Life is really...

218
00:15:41,748 --> 00:15:43,398
...Ephemeral.

219
00:15:43,914 --> 00:15:46,224
- Right?
- Right?
- Right?

220
00:15:49,806 --> 00:15:52,346
Why be so sentimental?

221
00:15:53,037 --> 00:15:55,787
Being sentimental doesn't suit you ladies.

222
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:57,200
You still have more...

223
00:15:57,535 --> 00:16:04,005
..."meters" or um... "kilometers",
there's still... so much more ahead...

224
00:16:05,970 --> 00:16:07,360
Eh? Oh, no!

225
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,720
Oh, God! You okay!

226
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,120
Kosuzu-san!

227
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:12,310
Ready, set...!

228
00:16:18,766 --> 00:16:22,144
Huh? Did you hear a firing shot?

229
00:16:22,386 --> 00:16:24,586
You're just hearing things.

230
00:16:27,511 --> 00:16:28,901
Shall we drink?

231
00:16:29,165 --> 00:16:31,125
We mustn't drink.

232
00:16:34,012 --> 00:16:37,749
Excuse me. There's some middle-aged guy
on the side of road, who dislocated his shoulder...

233
00:16:37,749 --> 00:16:39,589
...after high-fiving many people.

234
00:16:39,829 --> 00:16:42,969
He kept moaning,
"It popped out! It popped out!"

235
00:16:43,981 --> 00:16:46,644
Well, we better pop it back in!

236
00:16:46,644 --> 00:16:48,699
Yeah. Where's this guy.

237
00:16:48,699 --> 00:16:49,849
This way.

238
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:06,420
This isn't altogether bad either.

239
00:17:09,230 --> 00:17:11,120
Master, second helping of zoni, please!

240
00:17:11,120 --> 00:17:12,926
- Me, too!
- Me, too!

241
00:17:12,926 --> 00:17:14,529
Oh, me too!

242
00:17:14,539 --> 00:17:15,789
Sure thing!

243
00:17:18,902 --> 00:17:23,630
<i>At the end of the day, when people are rushing home...</i>

244
00:17:24,156 --> 00:17:26,676
<i>...That's when my day starts.</i>

245
00:17:27,809 --> 00:17:32,960
<i>My business hours start from midnight to 7 am.</i>

246
00:17:33,373 --> 00:17:36,783
<i>People call my restaurant 'the late night diner.'</i>

247
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,685
Master, is mine not ready yet?

248
00:17:39,685 --> 00:17:40,950
Ah, wait just a bit more.

249
00:17:40,950 --> 00:17:42,710
- Okay.
- It'll be ready soon.

250
00:17:51,998 --> 00:17:53,188
<i>Welcome.</i>

251
00:17:55,141 --> 00:17:56,541
<i>Good evening.</i>

252
00:17:58,571 --> 00:18:02,171
<i>Mm. It's really delicious.</i>

253
00:18:02,171 --> 00:18:04,161
<i>Is there anything you want?</i>

254
00:18:05,451 --> 00:18:09,241
<i>Could you sing "Don't Say Anything"
once again? For my wife.</i>

255
00:18:14,593 --> 00:18:17,793
<i>Master, give me menchi!</i>

256
00:18:20,051 --> 00:18:21,821
<i>Do you yourself find this interesting?</i>

257
00:18:22,487 --> 00:18:24,112
<i>To be honest, it's boring.</i>

258
00:18:24,405 --> 00:18:26,625
<i>You said that you'd quickly
become a mangaka and go pro!</i>

259
00:18:30,131 --> 00:18:35,631
<i>When the time comes that you feel you
really want to draw...then you should draw again.</i>

260
00:18:38,763 --> 00:18:41,053
<i>Can we see each other
with the premise of marriage?</i>

261
00:18:41,237 --> 00:18:45,437
<i>My feelings, you see...
are not that simple.</i>

262
00:18:48,766 --> 00:18:50,037
<i>Being scornful?</i>

263
00:18:50,037 --> 00:18:53,737
<i>If you do not become strong,
you won't live, right?</i>

264
00:18:56,082 --> 00:18:56,972
<i>President.</i>

265
00:19:00,282 --> 00:19:01,482
<i>Beniten.</i>

266
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:09,491
<i>My mom said..."Don't become
just a cheap mistress."</i>

267
00:19:15,030 --> 00:19:19,083
<i>The truth is I hated vermicelli salad.</i>

268
00:19:19,083 --> 00:19:22,772
<i>But since Shiga-kun loved it...</i>

269
00:19:23,309 --> 00:19:24,899
<i>...I thought, I'll come to like it, too I guess.</i>

270
00:19:25,357 --> 00:19:27,276
<i>Shiga-kun told me he loves me.</i>

271
00:19:27,276 --> 00:19:28,586
<i>What?</i>

272
00:19:31,179 --> 00:19:34,718
<i>Cabbage Rolls take time and effort.</i>

273
00:19:34,718 --> 00:19:37,280
<i>Your boobs were exactly like mine
when I was younger.</i>

274
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:41,488
<i>You're like a balloon who floated
from one man to another...</i>

275
00:19:41,488 --> 00:19:43,544
<i>You're not qualified to say
whether a man is good or bad!</i>

276
00:19:43,544 --> 00:19:46,848
<i>Your mother had taught me her recipe.</i>

277
00:19:46,848 --> 00:19:50,149
<i>I had wanted to eat
my mom's Cabbage Rolls.</i>

278
00:19:50,715 --> 00:19:51,855
<i>Thanks for waiting.</i>

279
00:19:52,341 --> 00:19:55,561
<i>Everyone says that freshwater clam soup is
a good midsummer dish for the body.</i>

280
00:19:56,398 --> 00:19:57,931
<i>Do you like Go?</i>

281
00:19:57,931 --> 00:20:01,829
<i>I have no idea how it goes.
I always fall asleep when watching it.</i>

282
00:20:02,108 --> 00:20:04,388
<i>It's possible that we may make
some stupid choices again...</i>

283
00:20:06,103 --> 00:20:08,399
<i>Can you give me a chance?</i>

284
00:20:11,366 --> 00:20:17,782
<i>If you don't properly get rid of the sand,
you won't be able to make delicious soup.</i>

285
00:20:17,782 --> 00:20:19,946
<i>Do you have Kinpira Gobo?</i>

286
00:20:21,874 --> 00:20:23,801
<i>But I love her so much!</i>

287
00:20:23,801 --> 00:20:24,731
<i>Ouch!</i>

288
00:20:25,624 --> 00:20:26,974
<i>Don't go!</i>

289
00:20:40,678 --> 00:20:42,707
<i>Mine's the Liver with Chives.</i>

290
00:20:42,707 --> 00:20:44,624
<i>And mine's the Chinese Chives with Liver.</i>

291
00:20:44,624 --> 00:20:46,788
<i>But you also look at me a bit lewdly...</i>

292
00:20:52,543 --> 00:20:54,778
<i>He's my fiance.</i>

293
00:20:54,778 --> 00:20:56,437
<i>Guragura kuru.</i>

294
00:20:59,493 --> 00:21:01,543
<i>This isn't altogether bad either.</i>

295
00:21:08,794 --> 00:21:10,724
Excuse me, excuse me please.

296
00:21:10,724 --> 00:21:12,194
Huh? What's happening?

297
00:21:12,194 --> 00:21:14,324
We just received a tip-off.

298
00:21:14,914 --> 00:21:16,454
They said it'll become a movie.

299
00:21:19,422 --> 00:21:21,512
Well, it's about time!

300
00:21:22,234 --> 00:21:26,944
If there's anything you like to order...
I'll make it if I can.

301
00:21:26,944 --> 00:21:29,167
Such is my business policy.

302
00:21:29,167 --> 00:21:34,257
If you ever come to this area...
and chance upon this "Meshi-ya"...

303
00:21:34,257 --> 00:21:36,717
...Feel free to come in!

